	"nodes":[
		{"id":"6edf1b300ed3ebc6","x":-520,"y":-720,"width":1000,"height":1040,"type":"text","text":"# Explain automation in natural language\n\nSame style as frontend/backend — for your **Tech stack — automation** slide.\n\n---\n\n## 30-second version\n\n> **Automation** is how users talk to my app **from Telegram** on their phone — without opening the website.\n>\n> They send a message in **Telegram**. **ngrok** gives my local **n8n** a public HTTPS address so Telegram can reach it. **n8n** runs in **Docker** on port **5678** and decides what to do — save an expense, ask a forecast question, or read a Plaid balance. Then n8n calls the same **Vercel API** as the web app — ledger, Plaid, forecast — and sends the reply back to Telegram.\n\n---\n\n## Walk through the slide (left to right)\n\n**1 — Telegram**  \n> “This is the **mobile interface**. The user texts things like ‘add expense grocery 85’ or ‘what is my checking balance?’ — same household finance questions, but from the phone.”\n\n**2 — ngrok (public HTTPS URL)**  \n> “Telegram lives on the internet; my n8n during development runs on my laptop. **ngrok** is a **tunnel** — it creates a public **HTTPS** link that forwards to n8n on port **5678**. Telegram requires HTTPS for webhooks, so ngrok is the bridge.”\n\n**3 — Docker (n8n :5678)**  \n> “**n8n** is the **automation brain** — workflows with an AI agent and HTTP tools. I run it in **Docker** so it’s always on port **5678**. n8n receives the message, picks the right tool, and formats the reply.”\n\n**4 — Vercel API (ledger, Plaid, forecast)**  \n> “n8n does **not** talk to the database directly. It calls my **Vercel API** — the same backend as the website — with a secure token. That keeps one source of truth: **Postgres on Neon**, same ledger math, same Plaid sync, same scenario chat logic.”\n\n---\n\n## Full round trip (say this slowly)\n\n```text\nPhone:  \"How much is on my credit card?\"\n   ↓\nTelegram sends webhook → ngrok HTTPS URL\n   ↓\nDocker n8n :5678 → AI agent chooses get_plaid_account_balances\n   ↓\nHTTP GET → Vercel /api/integrations/plaid/accounts\n   ↓\nAnswer text → n8n → Telegram reply on phone\n```\n\n---\n\n## Simple analogy\n\n> “**Telegram** is the customer on the phone. **ngrok** is the doorbell that rings your home office from the street. **n8n** is the assistant who hears the request and knows which script to run. **Vercel API** is the same company database the website uses — so phone and web never disagree.”\n\n---\n\n## Local dev vs production (if they ask)\n\n| | **Your slide (local dev)** | **Production option** |\n|---|---------------------------|------------------------|\n| n8n | Docker on your PC | n8n Cloud or Railway |\n| Tunnel | **ngrok** → `:5678` | Stable URL (no ngrok) |\n| API | **Vercel** (household-financial-web.vercel.app) | Same |\n\n> “For the course demo I use **local Docker n8n + ngrok** talking to **Vercel** in the cloud. I don’t need my laptop running the whole website — only n8n and ngrok if I want Telegram live.”\n\n---\n\n## Why automation is separate from frontend\n\n| | **Frontend** | **Automation** |\n|---|-------------|----------------|\n| User opens | Browser → `/ledger`, `/simulation` | Telegram app |\n| Orchestration | React pages | **n8n workflows** |\n| Backend | Same **Vercel API** | Same **Vercel API** |\n\n> “One backend, **two front doors** — web UI and Telegram.”\n\n---\n\n## Tie to your project story\n\n> “Automation matters because households need answers **on the go**. n8n handles the bot and routing; **Vercel** still owns the money logic. We even **evaluate** the Telegram agent with n8n datasets so it calls the right tool — ledger write vs Plaid vs forecast — and doesn’t invent numbers.”\n\n---\n\n## Common mistake to clarify (from your earlier slide)\n\n> “**ngrok does not replace n8n.** Docker **hosts** n8n. ngrok only **delivers** Telegram’s webhook to port 5678.”\n\n---\n\n## If someone asks: “Why not Telegram → Vercel directly?”\n\n> “You could for simple bots, but **n8n** gives a visual workflow, AI agent tools, evaluations, and scheduled jobs — like monthly Plaid sync — without rewriting everything in code.”\n\n---\n\n## One slide subtitle\n\n> **Automation:** Telegram → ngrok → n8n (Docker) → Vercel API → reply\n\n---\n\n## 15-second closing line\n\n> “So automation extends the same trustworthy backend to Telegram — mobile access, same ledger, same rules.”"}
